.TH "bathsearch" 1 "@BATH_DATE@" "BATH @BATH_VERSION@" "BATH Manual"

.SH NAME
bathsearch \- search a protein profile against a DNA sequence database


.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bathsearch
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I queryfile
.I seqdb


.SH DESCRIPTION

.PP
.B bathsearch
searches one or more protein profile HMMs against a DNA sequence
database, detecting homologous regions and producing alignments that
map back to the original DNA coordinates.

.PP
The
.I queryfile
may be a pre-built profile HMM file, a multiple sequence alignment
file, or an unaligned sequence file. If an alignment or sequence file
is provided,
.B bathsearch
builds a profile HMM on the fly before searching. To save the
produced HMM for later use, see the
.B \-\-hmmout
option.

.PP
.B bathsearch
supports three search modes:

.TP
.B Standard translation (default)
Translates the target DNA database into all six reading frames,
generating open reading frames (ORFs), then performs protein-to-protein
comparison followed by alignment back to the DNA coordinates. This mode
is best suited to well-annotated coding sequences.

.TP
.B Frameshift-aware (\-\-fs)
Converts the protein HMM into a codon-level HMM and performs
DNA-to-(quasi)codon alignment. This mode can detect and align through
frameshifts and stop codons caused by insertions, deletions, and
substitutions, making it suitable for noisy or pseudogene sequences.

.TP
.B Spliced alignment (\-\-splice)
Performs standard translation search followed by splice-site detection
for use with eukaryotic genomic sequences. Alignments can span introns,
and a per-exon output table is available with
.BR \-\-exontblout .

.PP
Either the
.I queryfile
or the target
.I seqdb
may be '\-' (a dash character), in which case that input is read from
stdin rather than a file. Only one input may come through stdin at a
time.

.PP
The output format is designed to be human-readable. The
.B \-\-tblout
option saves a concise tabular summary that is easier to parse. The
.B \-o
option redirects main output to a file.


.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.B \-h
Help; print a brief reminder of command line usage and all available
options.


.SH OPTIONS FOR CONTROLLING SEARCH MODE

.TP
.B \-\-fs
Use the frameshift-aware alignment pipeline. The protein HMM is
converted to a codon-level HMM that allows the alignment to span
frameshift errors and premature stop codons. Incompatible with
.BR \-\-splice .

.TP
.B \-\-splice
Use the spliced alignment pipeline. Standard translation search is
followed by splice-site detection, allowing alignments to span introns
in eukaryotic genomes. Incompatible with
.BR \-\-fs .


.SH OPTIONS FOR CONTROLLING OUTPUT

.TP
.BI \-o " <f>"
Direct the main human-readable output to a file
.I <f>
instead of the default stdout.

.TP
.BI \-\-tblout " <f>"
Save a simple tabular (space-delimited) file summarizing the per-target
output, with one data line per homologous region found.

.TP
.BI \-\-exontblout " <f>"
Save a parseable table of individual exons to file
.IR <f> .
Requires
.BR \-\-splice .

.TP
.BI \-\-fstblout " <f>"
Save a table of frameshift locations to file
.IR <f> .
Requires
.BR \-\-fs .

.TP
.BI \-\-hmmout " <f>"
When the query input is an alignment or sequence file, write the
profile HMM(s) constructed from that input to file
.IR <f> .

.TP
.B \-\-acc
Use accessions instead of names in the main output, where available
for profiles and/or sequences.

.TP
.B \-\-noali
Omit the alignment section from the main output. This can greatly
reduce the output volume.

.TP
.B \-\-notrans
Do not show the translated DNA sequence in the alignment display.

.TP
.B \-\-frameline
Include the reading frame of each codon in the alignment display.
Requires
.BR \-\-fs .

.TP
.B \-\-cigar
Include the alignment CIGAR string in tabular output. Requires
.BR \-\-tblout .

.TP
.B \-\-notextw
Unlimit the length of each line in the main output. The default
is a limit of 150 characters per line.

.TP
.BI \-\-textw " <n>"
Set the main output's line length limit to
.I <n>
characters per line (minimum 120). The default is 150.


.SH OPTIONS FOR TRANSLATION

.TP
.BI \-\-ct " <n>"
Use the alternate genetic code specified by NCBI translation table number
.IR <n> .
The default is 1 (the standard genetic code). A list of available
translation table numbers is printed at the end of the
.B \-h
help output.

.TP
.BI \-l " <n>"
Set the minimum ORF length to
.I <n>
residues. ORFs shorter than this are not considered. The default is 20.
Applies to standard translation mode.

.TP
.B \-m
ORFs must initiate with AUG only. Incompatible with
.BR \-M .

.TP
.B \-M
ORFs must initiate with any allowed initiation codon as defined by the
translation table. Incompatible with
.BR \-m .

.TP
.BI \-\-strand " <s>"
Translate only the specified strand. Choices are
.B plus
(forward strand only) or
.B minus
(reverse complement only). The default is
.B both
strands.


.SH OPTIONS FOR SPLICED ALIGNMENT

These options are only used in spliced alignment mode (requires
.BR \-\-splice ).

.TP
.BI \-\-min_intron " <n>"
Set the minimum allowed intron length to
.I <n>
nucleotides. The default is 13.

.TP
.BI \-\-max_intron " <n>"
Set the maximum allowed intron length to
.I <n>
nucleotides. The default is 200000.


.SH OPTIONS CONTROLLING REPORTING THRESHOLDS

Reporting thresholds control which hits appear in output. By default,
all hits with an E-value <= 10 are reported.

.TP
.BI \-E " <x>"
Report target sequences with an E-value <=
.IR <x> .
The default is 10.0.

.TP
.BI \-T " <x>"
Report target sequences with a bit score >=
.IR <x>
instead of using an E-value threshold.

.TP
.BI \-\-incE " <x>"
Use an E-value of <=
.I <x>
as the per-target inclusion threshold, the boundary between significant
("!") and marginal ("?") hits. The default is 0.01.

.TP
.BI \-\-incT " <x>"
Use a bit score of >=
.I <x>
as the per-target inclusion threshold instead of an E-value.


.SH OPTIONS CONTROLLING THE ACCELERATION PIPELINE

.B bathsearch
uses a multi-stage filter pipeline to accelerate searches. Standard
mode uses three stages: MSV, Viterbi, and Forward. Frameshift-aware
mode adds a fourth stage (FS-Forward) for hits that pass the first
three filters. Adjusting filter thresholds does not alter bit scores,
E-values, or alignments.

.TP
.B \-\-max
Turn off all filters and run full scoring on every target. Increases
sensitivity at a significant cost in speed.

.TP
.BI \-\-F1 " <x>"
Set the P-value threshold for the MSV filter stage. The default is 0.02.

.TP
.BI \-\-F2 " <x>"
Set the P-value threshold for the Viterbi filter stage. The default is 1e-3.

.TP
.BI \-\-F3 " <x>"
Set the P-value threshold for the Forward filter stage. The default is 1e-5.

.TP
.BI \-\-F4 " <x>"
Set the P-value threshold for the frameshift-aware Forward filter stage.
The default is 5e-4. Only used in frameshift mode (requires
.BR \-\-fs ).

.TP
.B \-\-nobias
Turn off the composition bias filter between the MSV and Viterbi stages.

.TP
.B \-\-nonull2
Turn off the null2 score corrections for biased composition.


.SH OPTIONS CONTROLLING THE SCORING SYSTEM

.TP
.B \-\-singlemx
When the query is a single sequence in an MSA format file, use a
substitution score matrix rather than the standard profile construction
method.

.TP
.BI \-\-popen " <x>"
Set the gap open probability to
.IR <x> .
The default is 0.02.

.TP
.BI \-\-pextend " <x>"
Set the gap extend probability to
.IR <x> .
The default is 0.4.

.TP
.BI \-\-mx " <s>"
Use the named built-in substitution score matrix. The default is BLOSUM62.
Available choices include PAM30, PAM70, PAM120, PAM240, BLOSUM45,
BLOSUM50, BLOSUM62, BLOSUM80, and BLOSUM90.

.TP
.BI \-\-mxfile " <f>"
Read a substitution score matrix from file
.IR <f> ,
in BLAST/FASTA matrix format. Incompatible with
.BR \-\-mx .


.SH OTHER OPTIONS

.TP
.BI \-Z " <x>"
Assert that the total size of the target database is
.I <x>
Megabases, for the purposes of E-value calculations, rather than the
actual size computed from the target file.

.TP
.BI \-\-seed " <n>"
Set the random number seed to
.IR <n> .
The default is 42 (reproducible). A value of 0 uses a randomly chosen
seed.

.TP
.BI \-\-w_beta " <x>"
Set the tail mass used to determine the window length parameter
.IR W .

.TP
.BI \-\-w_length " <n>"
Override the window length parameter
.I W
directly. Should be larger than the model length.

.TP
.BI \-\-qformat " <s>"
Assert that the query file is in format
.IR <s> ,
bypassing format autodetection. Accepts both sequence formats
(e.g., \fBfasta\fR) and alignment formats (e.g., \fBstockholm\fR).

.TP
.BI \-\-tformat " <s>"
Assert that the target database file is in format
.IR <s> ,
bypassing format autodetection. Common choices include
.BR fasta ,
.BR embl ,
.BR genbank .

.TP
.BI \-\-block_length " <n>"
Set the length of sequence blocks read from the target database in
multithreaded mode to
.I <n>
nucleotides. The default is chosen automatically.
(Only available when BATH is compiled with thread support.)

.TP
.BI \-\-cpu " <n>"
Set the number of parallel worker threads to
.IR <n> .
On multicore machines, the default is 2. The environment variable
.B HMMER_NCPU
also controls this.
(Only available when BATH is compiled with thread support.)


.SH SEE ALSO

.BR bathbuild (1),
.BR bathfetch (1),
.BR bathconvert (1),
.BR bathstat (1)

.PP
For complete documentation, see the BATH repository:
https://github.com/TravisWheelerLab/BATH


